                                          throws com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException,

        getWorkOrderAppointmentList API returns a list of work order appointments that satisfy the passed input criteria.

        Related Documents
        Input XML Input DTD Output XML Output DTD Error XML Error DTD

        User Exits: None

        Events Raised: None

        Audits: None

        Pre-condition: None

        Post-condition:
        A list of work order appointments that satisfy the input criteria is returned.

        Output Template Support: Yes.

        Database Extensibility Support: Not Supported for any nodes.

        Parameters:
        inXML - Required. Criteria for which a list of orders must be returned. For more information, see the associated input xml files.
        env - Required. Environment handle returned by the createEnvironment API.

        Returns:
        An XML document that contains a list of work order appointments. For details on the output, see the associated output files.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException - Java's default remote exception handler.
        com.yantra.yfs.japi.YFSException - Exception containing error codes in the standard error files.
